fields.description:
*Acceptance Criteria* 
* Customer is new/not logged in 
* Customer has previously completed 'About you' section AR-3029
* Fields: https://singlepointsolutions.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ARD/pages/2715713572/UBI+fields
* As it stands there are no current requirements to change these fields under the 'Your car' section 
* The user should have the option, as they do in car today, to change their registration if needed via the 'edit' function. 
*  As per user story AR-3026 A user will enter their car registration and two checks will be ran in the backend
# Standard applied vehicle look-up services
# The new API for vehicle compatibility
* The standard error handling for an invalid car registration should be applied displaying the following error message:
Sorry, we can't find your car. Please check the Registration Number you entered is correct using the format: 10D45001. Alternatively you can call us on 01 486 9775
* If a user enters a valid car registration, and it is not compatible with UBI insurance they will see the following:
* Design https://app.zeplin.io/project/5dc2eec3ce302d23dcdb888b/screen/607ebc3a9c93298dd8641bc6
* Once a user enters a registration number that is not compatible with the UBI insurance they will see the following copy:
Sorry, your car is not compatible with our mileage monitor therefore we cannot offer you a quote. Please follow select Car below to get a quote for an annual payment policy or alternatively you can call us on 01 486 9775.
* Once the user selects the hyperlink they are taken to the Motor product landing page

Your Contents is insured for  [Dynamic based on contents selected] - this field is not required for anyone who has selected 'Buildings cover' only

Loss or damage to your buildings and contents as a result of events such as fire, storm or flood

24 Hour Emergency Helpline

Replacement locks

Cover up to 650 for finding a water or oil leak

Your Liability cover for up to 3m as property owner or occupier

* Allianz Home Insurance IPID: hyperlink: https://www.arachas.ie/allianz-home-insurance-product-IPID

*Acceptance Criteria:*

* Requirement to split the Licence type and Country now that we will be integrating with Risk Handler.
* Under 'About you' after the question 'How many years have you been resident in Ireland' please add the following questions:

2 Full EU
3 Full UK
